I made it using agar powder, since I saw some people asking if you can use agar, I will share some advice for the substitions since I failed to do the recipe correctly when adding agar instead of gelatin sheet at first.

When you mix the cheese, the cream, the yogurt, the vanilla and the lemon juice, do it in a pot in low heat, in the order that Hidamari uses in the video. When it is about to boil, add the agar powder and don't stop mixing gently (don't use high heat! Be patient and let it boil in low heat). Leave it in the fire two more minutes mixing non stop and then let it cool just a bit, then put it in the mold and into the fridge. I employed 2g of agar but it can vary from mark to mark.

Then, the second step when doing the transparent layer, boil the water plus sugar and lemon but only boil the first half of the amount indicated and add another 2g of agar (I added less the first time and it didn't solidify). Pour it, refrigerate at least 30' as Hidamari said and then boil the rest of the water-sugar-lemon mix and add another 2g of agar. Pour it and let it rest (I waited a whole night).

It was my first time using agar and it finally went well! Thanks again for the recipe
